detail_description: Milky Way Cafe, a long-standing restaurant in Makati established in 1962, offers classic Filipino dishes such as their renowned Milky Way Kare Kare, Baby Crispy Pata, Bistek Tagalog, and Dinuguan at Puto. The establishment provides a nostalgic dining experience with traditional flavors. Originally a dairy bar in the 1950s, it has evolved into a go-to spot for Kapampangan cuisine.
name: Milky Way Cafe
address: Milkyway, 900 Antonio Arnaiz Ave, Makati City, 1200 Metro Manila, Philippines

detail_description: Sarsá Kitchen + Bar, led by renowned chef JP Anglo, is a strong advocate for Filipino cuisine and culture. During the pandemic, the restaurant showed support for healthcare workers, raised funds for typhoon victims, and provided aid to delivery couriers. They also collaborated with other local establishments to offer family meal sets and ready-to-cook kits featuring Negrense dishes that are not commonly found in the city.
name: Sarsá Kitchen + Bar
address: 109 Rada, Legazpi Village, Makati, 1229 Kalakhang Maynila, Philippines

excerpt: Eclectic decor restaurant offering traditional Filipino dishes including seafood & desserts.
detail_description: Cafe Juanita is a restaurant located in the West side of Kapitolyo, known for its eclectic decor and upscale dining experience. The ambience features hand-picked antiques that create a cohesive yet eccentric atmosphere. The menu offers traditional Filipino dishes with a twist, including seafood and desserts. The restaurant is ideal for family gatherings and romantic occasions, offering classic Filipino dishes like Ratatouille and Kare Kare.
name: Cafe Juanita
address: 19 W Capitol Dr, Pasig, 1603 Metro Manila, Philippines

detail_description: Locavore offers a modern twist on traditional Filipino dishes, providing elevated versions of familiar favorites. The restaurant is known for its progressive take on authentic cuisine, with standout dishes like the sizzling Sinigang and Oyster Sisig. One of their popular offerings is the Duck Lugaw, a generous serving of flavorful rice porridge topped with duck floss, fried garlic, spring onions, soft-boiled egg, and ginger oil.
name: Locavore
address: Three Central, Valero, Makati City, Metro Manila, Philippines

detail_description: Perched atop The Bayleaf Hotel in Intramuros, Manila, the Sky Deck View Bar is a must-visit for anyone looking to soak in breathtaking views while enjoying delicious food and drinks. This rooftop gem features an inviting al fresco lounge that provides a spectacular 360-degree panorama of the Manila skyline, historical landmarks like Fort Santiago and the National Museum, as well as lush greenery from the nearby golf course.
name: Sky Deck
address: HXRH+2G3, The Bayleaf, Muralla St, Intramuros, Manila, 1002 Metro Manila, Philippines

detail_description: Toyo Eatery is a renowned Filipino restaurant known for its innovative take on traditional Filipino cuisine. Despite the challenges, Toyo Eatery and its sister bakeshop, Panaderya Toyo, have continued to impress with whimsical bilao sets featuring barbecue skewers and signature silog fried rice. Chef Jordy Navarra's creativity has once again captured the attention of food enthusiasts as he prepares to host the Philippine leg of the global food event Gelinaz!
name: Toyo Eatery
address: 2316, The Alley at Karrivin, Karrivin Plaza, 1231 Chino Roces Ave Ext, Makati City, Metro Manila, Philippines

excerpt: Sleek quarters, some with butler service, in a high-end hotel with 7 bars & restaurants, plus a spa.
detail_description: Nestled in the vibrant Bonifacio Global City, Grand Hyatt Manila is a luxurious haven that offers an array of sleek accommodations, some even featuring butler service for that extra touch of indulgence. Guests can indulge their taste buds at any of the seven bars and restaurants on-site, each providing a unique dining experience. For those seeking relaxation, the hotel boasts a serene spa where you can unwind after exploring the bustling city.
name: Grand Hyatt Manila
address: 8th Avenue, corner 35th St, Bonifacio Global City, Taguig, 1634 Metro Manila, Philippines

detail_description: Antonio's Restaurant is a popular dining spot located in Tagaytay, Cavite. The restaurant offers a charming al-fresco area and has a cozy vibe with plenty of windows allowing natural light to filter in. It is pet-friendly, welcoming vaccinated pets that are well-behaved and leashed or in carriers. The menu features delectable dishes such as the Smoked Salmon Benedict and Fresh Corned Beef with Provencale Sauce, both highly recommended options.
name: Antonio's Restaurant
address: PUROK 138, 3VVX+5F8, Barangay, Neogan, Tagaytay City, Cavite, Philippines

detail_description: El Union Coffee is a popular coffee spot in the heart of Urbiztondo, Philippines. It started as a small corner cafe and has now expanded into a two-storey lounge where visitors can enjoy expertly roasted and thoughtfully prepared coffee. The menu includes hot lattes, cold-brew mochas, and dirty horchata. Additionally, patrons can indulge in fluffy Indoor Smores or the huge Skillet Cookie while attending workshops or social events on the second floor.
name: El Union Coffee
address: M85C+VVW, MacArthur National Highway, San Juan, La Union, Philippines

detail_description: People's Palace offers a modern take on Thai cuisine in Makati, serving expertly prepared dishes with fresh ingredients and organic vegetables. The restaurant is known for its stunning surroundings, excellent service, and consistently delicious Thai fare. One of their standout dishes is the yam som o, or pomelo salad, featuring juicy citrus wedges paired with prawns, shredded chicken, fresh herbs, and a lime-coconut dressing.
name: People's Palace
address: Greenbelt 3, Esperanza St, Makati City, 1223 Metro Manila, Philippines

detail_description: La Cathedral Cafe is a charming alfresco spot located in the heart of Intramuros, offering stunning views of the historic Manila Cathedral. With its European rooftop restaurant ambiance, it provides a picturesque setting for casual gatherings or romantic dates. The cafe's old-world vibes and panoramic vistas make diners feel like they've been transported to another part of the world.
name: La Cathedral Cafe
address: 636 Cabildo St, Intramuros, Manila, 1002 Metro Manila, Philippines

excerpt: Relaxed cottages in a quaint bed-and-breakfast offering a rustic-chic restaurant & a spa
detail_description: Nestled in the charming town of Alfonso, Cavite, Sonya's Garden is a delightful retreat that perfectly blends romance and relaxation. This enchanting bed-and-breakfast features cozy cottages and a rustic-chic restaurant renowned for its healthy meals crafted from organic produce grown on-site. Guests can indulge in freshly baked goods at Panaderia or unwind at the spa after a day filled with unique experiences like firefly watching, trekking through lush landscapes, or exploring the Proposal Garden and Secret River.
name: Sonya's Garden
address: Buck Estate Road, Alfonso, Cavite, Philippines

excerpt: Traditional Filipino cuisine served in an old-school, Spanish-style venue with antique decor.
detail_description: Ilustrado Restaurant is a renowned dining spot located in the heart of historic Intramuros in Manila. Housed in a charming heritage building, it offers a romantic setting with antique decor and lush surroundings, making it popular for tourists and wedding venues. The menu features a mix of Spanish, Filipino, and global cuisines, including traditional dishes like callos Madrilena and jamon serrano alongside favorites like caesar salad and Canadian maple-glazed baby back ribs.
name: Ilustrado Restaurant
address: 744 Cabildo Street, corner Recoletos St, Intramuros, City Of Manila, 1002 Metro Manila, Philippines

detail_description: Harbor View Restaurant, established in 1985, is a popular spot known for its fresh and reasonably priced seafood served in a laid-back and welcoming setting. Situated against the backdrop of Manila Bay's picturesque views, it offers an ideal setting for a romantic dinner or a casual gathering with friends. The menu features an enticing fusion of Asian and Western dishes, with the spotlight on their impressive selection of seafood.
name: Harbor View Restaurant
address: South Dr, Ermita, City Of Manila, 1000 Metro Manila, Philippines

detail_description: Le Petit Soufflé is a French-Japanese bistro located in Century City Mall, offering a cozy and hip ambiance. The restaurant is known for its innovative and exquisite dishes, with must-tries including the indulgent Mac & Foie and the best-selling Valrhona Guanaja Chocolate Souffle. Their Classic Souffle Pancake with cream cheese is also a popular choice.
name: Le Petit Soufflé
address: 3F Century City Mall, Kalayaan Ave, Makati, 1210 Metro Manila, Philippines

detail_description: Lampara is a popular dining spot in the vibrant Poblacion district, known for its innovative neo-Filipino cuisine and creative cocktails. Despite the challenges brought on by the pandemic, Lampara persevered and even introduced new offerings like Lite by Lampara meal subscriptions and bottled cocktails for at-home enjoyment. Set in a renovated apartment complex, the restaurant offers al fresco dining with both enclosed and open-air sections, making it a top choice for outdoor dining in Manila.
name: Lampara
address: 5883 Enriquez, Makati City, 1210 Metro Manila, Philippines

detail_description: Rambla is a Spanish-Mediterranean restaurant located in the Rockwell neighborhood, offering a delightful dining experience. The restaurant features a variety of seating options suitable for any occasion, including special events on the second level, cozy booths for gatherings with friends, and a bar area with views into the open kitchen.
name: Rambla
address: Joya Tower, 28 Plaza Dr, Makati City, 1210 Metro Manila, Philippines

detail_description: Lorenzo's Way is a restaurant that pays homage to its late founder, Lorenzo J. Cruz, offering Filipino-European dishes including family heirloom recipes. The menu features classic dishes like kare-kare and experimental ones like pork sinigang infused with kamias and langka. With only two locations, both offer al fresco dining areas. The restaurant is known for its chic furniture and northern Filipino dishes from Pampanga with a Spanish twist.
name: Lorenzo's Way
address: Greenbelt, Legaspi Street, Makati City, 1209 Metro Manila, Philippines

detail_description: a mano Rockwell is a popular Italian restaurant that prides itself on serving fresh and authentic Italian dishes from various regions of Italy. Their specialty lies in their pizzas, which are made with Caputo Tipo 00 flour and cooked in a Valoriani oven to achieve a thin and chewy crust. The menu offers a wide variety of toppings, ranging from classic options like Margherita con Bufala to more unique choices like the 'Carbonara' Pizza.
name: a mano Rockwell
address: R1 Level (Stall 144, Power Plant Mall, Rockwell Center, Makati City, Metro Manila, Philippines

detail_description: Nestled in the vibrant heart of Makati, Kyo-to Kaiseki invites you to embark on an exquisite culinary journey through the art of traditional kaiseki dining. This Japanese restaurant is a haven for food enthusiasts seeking an authentic experience, where each meticulously crafted multi-course meal reflects a perfect balance of taste, texture, and seasonal ingredients. At Kyo-to, every dish is not just a feast for the palate but also a visual delight, showcasing the elegance inherent in Japanese haute cuisine.
name: Kyō To
address: G/F Coyiuto House, 119 C. Palanca Street, 1229 Don Carlos Palanca, Legazpi Village, Makati City, Metro Manila, Philippines

detail_description: Metronome, a renowned restaurant, faced challenges with its dine-in operations due to the lack of an outdoor dining area. However, the team behind the acclaimed establishment launched Lazy Oeuf in 2020 to continue serving their loyal patrons with gourmet takeaway offerings. The sister brand offers a delectable array of dishes such as French onion burgers with foie gras, croissant sandwiches, and indulgent desserts.
name: Metronome
address: 160 Bolanos, Legazpi Village, Makati City, 1229 Metro Manila, Philippines

detail_description: The Wholesome Table Salcedo, a restaurant and bakery, temporarily closed its branches due to the pandemic but has since reopened for dine-in, take-out, and delivery. The establishment prides itself on serving unprocessed and toxin-free food such as free-range poultry, grass-fed beef, and wild-caught seafood. In addition to salads and sandwiches, the menu also features comfort food like pastas, wood-fired pizzas, pancakes, crispy calamari, and pork chops.
name: The Wholesome Table Salcedo
address: Salcedo Village, The Infinity Tower H.V. Dela Costa, Corner L.P. Leviste Street, Street, Makati, 1227 Metro Manila, Philippines

detail_description: Romulo Café is a popular Filipino restaurant named after Carlos P. Romulo, a renowned journalist and diplomat. With multiple branches across the city, it offers authentic home-cooked Filipino dishes that have been passed down through generations. The restaurant takes pride in its traditional and innovative dishes, prepared with technical skill and precision.
name: Romulo Café
address: Lazcano cor., Sct. Tuazon Brgy. Tomas Morato, 32 Sct. Dr. Lazcano St, Diliman, Quezon City, Metro Manila, Philippines

detail_description: The Aristocrat Restaurant is a beloved dining establishment known for its Filipino-style barbecue chicken and rich history. Since the 1930s, it has been a cherished fine-dining venue in Manila, offering iconic dishes such as adobo flying saucer, lumpiang ubod sariwa, puto at dinuguan, Aristocrat pancit canton, and arroz con caldo with beef tripe. Originally located in Malate, it has expanded to multiple cities nearby.
name: The Aristocrat Restaurant
address: 432, 1004 San Andres St, Malate, City Of Manila, 1004 Metro Manila, Philippines

detail_description: Kanin Club is a must-visit for anyone eager to indulge in authentic Filipino flavors. This charming restaurant offers an extensive menu filled with traditional dishes, each crafted with a modern twist that elevates the dining experience. From the rich and savory adobo to the refreshing kinilaw, every bite at Kanin Club celebrates the diverse culinary heritage of the Philippines. If you're a rice lover, this spot is paradise!
name: Kanin Club
address: H24F+FMW, Ayala Triangle Gardens, Makati Ave, Makati, 1209 Metro Manila, Philippines

detail_description: Located in The Social food park in Poblacion, Makati, Crosta Pizzeria is known for its sourdough pizzas with an airy and chewy crust. The menu features creatively named pizzas like the Basic Bitch and Tickle Pickle, as well as a range of vegan options such as the Death by Hummucide and Vegan Shroomed Out.
name: Crosta Pizzeria
address: Salcedo Village, 104 HV Dela Costa, Cor L.P. Leviste Street, Makati City, Metro Manila, Philippines

detail_description: Chef Laudico Guevarra's is a renowned restaurant located in San Juan City, housed in a charming heritage house that has been hosting various events since the 1920s. The restaurant offers an affordable and high-quality Filipino buffet experience within the converted heritage home. Chef Laudico Guevarra's is known for its inviting ambiance, diverse food selection, and reasonable rates for both lunch and dinner.
name: Guevarra's by Chef Laudico
address: 387 P. Guevarra St, cor Argonne, San Juan, 1500 Metro Manila, Philippines

detail_description: Tsukiji is a renowned Japanese restaurant located in Metro Manila, known for its top-quality sushi and sashimi. The restaurant takes pride in sourcing ingredients from the famous Tsukiji Market in Tokyo, with fish flown in from Japan at least three times a week. The head chef, Toshiro Okajima, started his career at the Tsukiji Market and now oversees the sushi counter at Tsukiji Restaurant.
name: Tsukiji
address: 3rd Floor, Milky Way Building, 900 Antonio Arnaiz Ave, Makati City, 1200 Metro Manila, Philippines

detail_description: Flossom Kitchen + Cafe is a trendy and beautiful brunch spot nestled in San Juan City. The cafe boasts sweet, garden-inspired interiors that are perfect for Instagram-worthy photos. Their diverse menu features a mix of Filipino and Western cuisines, with highlights such as the creamy Avocado Toast, Smoked Salmon Benedict, and lip-smacking Honey Chorizo Pasta.
name: Flossom Kitchen + Cafe
address: 187 N Averilla, San Juan City, 1500 Metro Manila, Philippines

detail_description: Isdaan Floating Restaurant in Calauan is a captivating dining spot that promises an unforgettable experience for food lovers and nature enthusiasts alike. Nestled amidst lush greenery and tranquil fishponds, this unique restaurant allows guests to dine on bamboo rafts while indulging in a variety of mouth-watering Filipino dishes, from fresh seafood to beloved classics like crispy pata and sinigang.
name: Isdaan Floating Restaurant
address: 58G2+XQ5, National Hwy, Bay, Laguna, Philippines

detail_description: Hapag, located in the Katipunan area, offers an 8-course tasting menu featuring contemporary Filipino dishes like Laing Stones and Banana Heart Granola. The restaurant provides a wide array of entree options compared to other tasting menus. With minimalist interiors, it offers an intimate dining experience perfect for special occasions. The refined take on Filipino favorites is both visually appealing and delicious. Reservations are necessary, and guests can check social media for updated menus and schedules.
name: Hapag
address: 7th Floor, The Balmori Suites, Hidalgo Dr, Rockwell Center, Makati City, 1210 Metro Manila, Philippines

detail_description: Victorino's Restaurant is a delightful gem nestled in the vibrant heart of Quezon City, perfect for those craving authentic Ilocano flavors without the long journey to the north. This charming eatery is run by siblings DV Savellano and Queenie Paras, who bring their heritage from Ilocos Sur to life through a menu filled with traditional dishes.
name: Victorino's Restaurant
address: 11th Jamboree, Diliman, Quezon City, Metro Manila, Philippines

detail_description: Tahanan Bistro is a dining establishment located in Binangonan, Rizal, Philippines. Despite mixed reviews from Google users, it is listed among the top restaurants in the area. The bistro offers a unique dining experience and is situated within reasonable proximity to Thunderbird Resorts Rizal. It stands out among other nearby eateries and provides an opportunity for visitors to enjoy Filipino cuisine in a distinct setting.
name: Tahanan Bistro
address: 22 Loresville Drive, Lores Farm Subdivision, Antipolo City, 1870 Lalawigan ng Rizal, Philippines

excerpt: Modest dorms & private rooms in a relaxed beachfront hostel offering surf lessons & an eatery/bar.
detail_description: Flotsam & Jetsam Artist Beach Hostel is a popular beachfront accommodation in La Union, known for its relaxed atmosphere and vibrant crowd. The hostel offers modest dorms and private rooms, making it an ideal choice for travelers seeking a laid-back beach experience. In addition to providing surf lessons, the hostel features an eatery and bar where guests can socialize and enjoy the eclectic ambiance.
name: Flotsam & Jetsam Hostel
address: M86F+PV2, MacArthur Hwy, San Juan, La Union, Philippines

detail_description: Halo-Halo de Iloko is a well-known Filipino dessert and snack that features a delightful mix of preserved fruits, sweetened legumes, gels, crushed ice, and evaporated milk. The dish encourages diners to blend all the ingredients together for an enjoyable experience. While there may be debates about its exact ingredients, the variation depends on the creator's preferences.
name: Halo-Halo de Iloko
address: J8HF+VJG, Zandueta St, San Fernando City, La Union, Philippines

detail_description: Kabsat in La Union has quickly become a favorite dining spot, with its name meaning 'sibling' in Ilocano. This spacious restaurant and bar provides a cozy atmosphere for families and friends to enjoy meals together. Situated on a 1500-square-meter area, Kabsat offers a homey ambiance perfect for beach hangouts, especially during the colorful sunset.
name: Kabsat La Union
address: M87G+453, San Juan, La Union, Philippines

detail_description: Makai Bowls is a popular spot in the coastal commune of San Juan, situated at the Great Northwest Philippine Travel Stop and Viewing Deck, offering stunning sea views. It was established to provide surfers and beach enthusiasts with a healthy dining option. Known for its dairy-free and sugar-free smoothie bowls made from 100% real fruits, Makai Bowls has relocated from Flotsam & Jetsam Hostel to its own place at the Travel Stop.
name: Makai Bowls
address: San Juan, La Union, Philippines

detail_description: The Cabin Cafe is a rustic cafe located in a peaceful forest. They offer home cooked meals in simple teepee booths, which will leave you feeling energized and refreshed.
name: The Cabin Cafe
address: Unnamed Road, San Jose, Tarlac, Philippines

name: Masa Bakehouse La Union
address: Barangay, Costales st. Sitio Dappat, San Juan, 2514 La Union, Philippines

detail_description: Located along Urbiztondo Road in San Juan La Union, BeachBum Food Park is a unique dining destination that offers a casual and laid-back atmosphere. It's not about luxury, but rather about enjoying outdoor dining, tasty food, and affordable beer. The park is particularly popular among visitors looking for a vibrant nightspot. Operating from Monday to Sunday with extended hours on weekends, it provides an ideal setting for socializing over delicious meals and drinks.
name: BeachBum Food Park
address: M85C+HWG, Urbiztondo Rd, San Juan, La Union, Philippines

detail_description: Sabong Fried Chicken is a cozy spot in the Great Northwest complex that's perfect for satisfying your fried chicken cravings. The menu is simple yet enticing, offering four types of chicken with four different sauces and a variety of sides. You can indulge in their Original Sabong Fried Chicken served with hand-cut fries and homemade banana ketchup, or try the kare-kare inspired version with honey-bagoong glaze, kare-kare sauce, and eggplant salsa.
name: Sabong Fried Chicken
address: National Highway, San Juan, 2514 La Union, Philippines

detail_description: Mad Monkeys Burger Lab is a laid-back burger joint located along McArthur Highway in San Juan La Union. Despite its unassuming stall setup near Urbiztondo, the place exudes chill vibes with open-air ambiance and good music. The menu is intentionally small, focusing on their big and flavorful burger dishes. One of their unique offerings is the SOS sauce, a blend of roasted garlic and spices created by the owners.
name: Mad Monkeys Burger Lab
address: M84C+HG2, Brgy. Urbiztondo, Manila, North Road, San Juan, La Union, Philippines

detail_description: Papa Bear is a cozy restaurant located in La Union, offering a diverse menu featuring Asian cuisine. The establishment takes pride in its themed dishes that showcase the flavors of Southeast Asian countries such as char kway teow, pho, and sambal pork. One of their signature offerings is the begg bowl, priced at just under two hundred pesos.
name: Papa Bear
address: The Great Northwest Philippines Travel Stop and Viewing Deck, MacArthur Hwy, San Juan, La Union, Philippines

detail_description: Gefseis Greek Grill & Restaurant is a must-visit spot in La Union, highly recommended by social media influencers and bloggers. The restaurant's ambiance is inspired by Santorini, Greece, and it offers a rare opportunity to savor Greek cuisine in the country. Located right by the beach, this open-air blue-and-white restaurant boasts an extensive menu featuring fresh and healthy options with a focus on grilled meats and vegetables.
name: Gefseis Greek Grill
address: Urbiztondo Beach Urbiztondo, San Juan, 2514 La Union, Philippines

detail_description: Abe is a Filipino restaurant under the LJC Restaurants brand, paying homage to the owner's well-traveled artist-writer father who had a passion for food. The restaurant offers an ambiance reminiscent of a Filipino get-together, with dishes meant for sharing. Despite some delays in serving food due to high demand, the staff are friendly and accommodating.
name: Abe
address: 11th Ave, Taguig City, 1634 Metro Manila, Philippines

detail_description: Hardin sa Paraiso Grill & Restaurant is a popular dining spot in Binalonan, Pangasinan, Philippines. It is known for its delicious Asian cuisine and seafood dishes. The restaurant offers a relaxing atmosphere where visitors can enjoy good food and hang out with friends or family. Located in a convenient area, it provides an ideal setting for travelers to indulge in local flavors and unwind after exploring the beautiful province of Pangasinan.
name: Hardin sa Paraiso Grill & Restaurant
address: Town of Manaoag Zone, 6 Brgy. Lelemaan, Manaoag, 2430 Pangasinan, Philippines

detail_description: Mesa Filipino Moderne is a delightful dining destination that beautifully captures the essence of Filipino cuisine. Founded by the dynamic duo, Sharon Cuneta and Sen. Francis Kiko Pangilinan, this restaurant serves up beloved traditional dishes like sinigang, laing, and lechon with a modern twist. The ambiance reflects contemporary interpretations of classic Filipino home design, making it an inviting space to enjoy your meal.
name: Mesa Filipino Moderne
address: SM Mall of Asia, Seaside Blvd, Pasay, Metro Manila, Philippines

detail_description: Sungayan Grill is a must-visit restaurant in Bolinao, known for its boodle fights featuring fresh seafood, best enjoyed during a river cruise along Balingasay River. The experience is reminiscent of the river tours in Loboc and Loay in Bohol. Families and groups of friends visiting Bolinao should not miss this unique dining experience.
name: Sungayan Grill
address: 9V34+Q2W, Bolinao, Pangasinan, Philippines

detail_description: Provenciano, located in Quezon City, is a popular Filipino restaurant offering a wide array of authentic regional dishes from various provinces in the Philippines. The name 'Provenciano' reflects its commitment to serving traditional cuisine found in rural areas. The menu features carefully curated specialties such as sinaing na tulingan, a slow-cooked mackerel wrapped in banana leaves and boiled with kamias for a subtle sourness.
name: Provenciano
address: 110 Maginhawa, Diliman, Quezon City, 1101 Metro Manila, Philippines

detail_description: Located in Pasig, Sentro 1771 has been a pioneer in elevating traditional Filipino cuisine with a modern twist for nearly two decades. The restaurant is known for its signature dishes that take everyday Filipino viands to the next level, such as their innovative preparation of galunggong. By infusing Western and Asian influences into local dishes, Sentro 1771 offers unique creations like Corned Beef Sinigang and Rated GG.
name: Sentro 1771 (Restaurant and Events Place)
address: Camino Verde Rd, Pasig City, Metro Manila, Philippines
